_info_definition.iso_639_3_eng: Default namespace for all core terms and descriptors of the data dictionary.

_info_description.iso_639_3_eng:
This *root namespace* is resenved to *terms* and *descriptors* that constitute the *core* of the *data dictionary*. This namespace should *not* be *used* for *data*, it should *only* be *used* for *dictionary* related *items*; this includes using it as a *parent namespace*.

The local identifier of this term is *empty*, which is *invalid*: this was done on purpose to prevent users from using this namespace, because a term with an empty global identifier cannot exist. Since its global identifier is empty, all terms and descriptors under this namespace will have a global identifier that starts with the underscore separator token, a feature unique to dictionary terms and descriptors.

_info_definition.iso_639_3_eng: This wildcard term represents any term.

_info_description.iso_639_3_eng: This *namespace* is used as a *wildcard* to indicate *any term*.

_info_definition.iso_639_3_eng: This wildcard term represents any descriptor.

_info_description.iso_639_3_eng: This *namespace* is used as a *wildcard* to indicate *any descriptor*. *Descriptors* are *terms* that *include* the `_data_class` and `_data_coontainer` *properties*.

This *namespace* is used by all *terms* and *descriptors*, constituting the *core* of the *data dictionary*, which are related to the *identification* and *naming* of *data dictionary items*.

This namespace is *reserved* for dictionary curation.

This *namespace* is used by all *terms* and *descriptors*, constituting the *core* of the *data dictionary*, which are involved in the *definition* of *descriptor data*. All terms and descriptors that indicate the *type*, *format* and *constraints* of data belong to this namespace.

This namespace is *reserved* for dictionary curation.

This *namespace* is used by all *terms* and *descriptors*, constituting the *core* of the *data dictionary*, which are involved in *documentation*. By documentation it is intended *descriptions* and *definitions* aimed at users of the data dictionary.

This namespace is *reserved* for dictionary curation.

This *namespace* is used by all *terms* and *descriptors*, constituting the *core* of the *data dictionary*, which are involved in *graph edges*. These items serve the purpose of *qualifying* the *relationship* between *nodes* in a *graph*.

This namespace is *reserved* for dictionary curation.

This *namespace* is used by all *terms* and *descriptors*, constituting the *core* of the *data dictionary*, which are involved in *defining rules* that determine if a *data structure* or *object* is *valid* and how it is *constructed*.

This namespace is *reserved* for dictionary curation.

This *namespace* is used by all *terms* and *descriptors*, constituting the *core* of the *data dictionary*, which are involved in *defining object data structures*. Terms of this type are considered *object structure types*.

This namespace is *reserved* for dictionary curation.
